Cape Town - Following an investigation by the police together with Department of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries (DAFF) a search was conducted Wednesday afternoon at two residences in Milnerton Ridge. At 14:00 police simultaneously searched two houses situated close to each other. In Bloemfontein street, they seized 368 units of dry abalone with an estimated value of R184Â 000 where a man was arrested. At the other residence in Fairview Street police arrested a Chinese man after a large variety of illegal ivory products to the value of R2.5 million were recovered. The two men aged 49 and 53 years old are expected to appear in the Cape Town Magistrates' Court on Friday, 2018-11-23. The Western Cape Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula praised the members for their dedication in ensuring that those who steal our maritime resources are brought to book. argusnews@inl.co.za Cape Argus